post_text:
Good afternoon Van Horn Lady Eagle Volleyball fans! Here are some quick notes in regards to the games at home:
-face coverings must be worn when in the building
-temperature checks will be taken upon entry
-home fans will enter from the west entrance of the gym foyer and sit on the home side
-visiting fans will enter from the east side of the gym foyer and sit on the visitor side
-there is limited seating on a first come first served basis.
-you must have a ticket to enter the gym
-tickets will be available from the ticket holders at each entrance.
-one ticket per person regardless of age
-once all tickets are passed out nobody else will be allowed to enter
-there will be no spectators on the gym floor before, during or after games.
-wear red, be loud and be proud!!!
#eagleprideneverdies

post_text:
Locker Clean Out and Pick Up

Parents/Guardians:

* Pick up will be from 9:00am -12:00 (noon), Tuesday, August 25, 2020 thru Friday, August 28, 2020, for grades 6 - 12 only.

* Parents will drive up and enter the bus drop off, located between both gyms off of 7th street, a monitor will come up to the vehicle and the student will tell them the locker # they were assigned last school year, if the student does not remember their locker #, the monitor will have a list of all students and locker numbers assigned

* A monitor will then go to the auxiliary gym and get the plastic bag associated with that locker #, and place it on the curb for the student to put inside the vehicle, monitors will not be allowed to open vehicle doors or vehicle trunks.

Respectfully,
Charles E. Gonzalez
Principal
Van Horn Schools

post_text: ATTENTION senior families and friends!! The Van Horn High School yearbook class is selling senior ads for anyone who is interested in purchasing a personalized message to congratulate your special senior in the yearbook. If you would like to purchase a senior ad please fill out the senior ad order form and email it to yearbook advisor Kianna Fierro at kfierro@ccaisd.net. All payments are to be mailed to the school address PO BOX 899 Van Horn, TX 79855 and all checks need to be made payable to CCAISD - Yearbook. The deadline to purchase a senior ad is May 18th. For any questions or concerns please email Kianna Fierro at kfierro@ccaisd.net. On behalf of the yearbook class, we would like to thank you for your consideration and we hope everyone is staying safe.

Devin Ortega

Both Devin and Arely recently completed a video highlighting the STEM programs at CCAISD, which helped secure a $75,000 grant from Chevron.

post_text:
Seniors 2020 by Coach Brock Tyrrell

To The class of 2020
We take our hats of to thee
For you were forced to sit out
And wonder why now, why me?
You worked hard for all four years
your senior to be the best.
But in a flash it was torn from you leaving an aching in your chest.
We may not know how you feel but know this one thing is true,
Your teachers and your coaches will always be here for you.
We‚Äôve loved you from day one this will never change
So look forward to the future and broaden your visual range.
And as you move on and life gives you it‚Äôs troubles and it‚Äôs tries
Think back to your time in Van Horn and remember
Eagle Pride Never Dies
#eagleprideneverdies
#classof2020

Wednesday‚Äôs WOD is here:
EMOM (Every Minute On The Minute)
Total time is 10 minutes
Start a timer, complete 20 Air Squats and then jog in place for the rest of the minute. At the 2:00 mark complete 20 more air squats and then jog in place for the rest of the minute. Repeat process until you have completed it for 10 total minutes. Have fun and challenge someone to do it with you! ü¶Ö üí™

post_text:
The Lady Eagles were on the road today to take on the Kermit Yellow Jackets and the Pecos Eagles. The JV team struggled a bit today. They had some good plays; however, their lack of communication took its toll in the end. We will continue to work with the JV team to build confidence and mental endurance. Keep working hard JV!

The Varsity team came out in full swing! We made a few changes on the defensive side as Amaya continues to heal. This team has really had to step it up and come together. They are now showing some tremendous resiliency, something we have lacked all season. We played back to back matches today and defeated the Kermit Yellow Jackets and the Pecos Eagles! We played a total of 7 sets today and only lost one. We look ahead as we set our sights on District play just one week away. We will continue to work hard and work together. That's the only way to win. GO EAGLES!!üí™üèΩü¶Öüèê #eagleprideneverdies
~Coach Urias

post_text:
The Lady Eagle JV Volleyball Team traveled this weekend to Wink to compete in their first tournament of the season. They played outstanding during their pool play on Friday and earned their spot in the Championship Bracket. During pool play, they played tough and their passing and communication was great. They have been working extremely hard on learning the new rotations and their defense came through.

They faced Kermit and Midland Classical on day two of the tournament, but fell short in both matches. Unfortunately, frustration set in a bit along with some lack of confidence. However, the JV girls continue to work hard and work well together. We will continue to build their confidence and work on their mental toughness. As coaches, we will continue to raise the bar.

Coach K continues to set high standards for her girls as she works on getting them ready for the next level. Coach K coached her team up this weekend and did a great job with her team. We look ahead to Tuesday as we go on the road to take on the Tornillo Lady Coyotes. #eagleprideneverdies
~Coach Urias

post_text: Five members of the Soaring Eagle Band Student Leadership Team participate in student day leadership training at the Texas Bandmasters Association Clinic and Convention in San Antonio. Pictured are Alexis Buford, Drum Major Daisy De la O, Israel Tarango, David Seijas, and Maria Sanchez. Over one thousand students from across Texas participated in this exciting event.

After a 3 hour rain delay your Van Horn Eagles finished pool play with 2 wins and 1 loss. They lost to Dangerfield 27-7 but came back and defeated Albany 28-6!!! We finished pool play in the #2 spot!! Bracket play for tomorrow will be posted later this evening when all pool play is finished. Keep up the great work men!!
